article.headline: Oregon State 56, UCLA 52
article.story:
LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Casey Nash scored 18 points and Judie Lomax
had 11 points and 11 rebounds as Oregon State snapped a five-game
losing streak with a 56-52 win over UCLA on Friday.

Nash, the leading scorer in the Pac-10, scored eight consecutive
points to open the second half and give the Beavers the lead for
good.

Judie Lomax went 5-for-5 from the field for Oregon State (6-6,
1-2).

Noelle Quinn led UCLA (8-9, 2-3) with 13 points and eight
rebounds.
